s &quot;why did they do this and how can anyone defend it&quot;... to which some people try to defend it.  Nobody should say &quot;this is fine, Clerics should have bigger nukes&quot; not now, not ever.  That's silly and the game isn't better for it - while it would be nearly unchanged if they fixed it RIGHT NOW.<br>
<br>
Saying &quot;if you take everything into account Wizards technically on a spreadsheet by a small margin have superior blasts&quot; is just silly, its like saying technically a honda is faster than a Jaguar because it takes less fuel to drive at 55 mph.  Technicalities can go to hell, its clear to me that any class built around combat fast blasting damage should have a clear margin of superiority over any class that is not, ESPECIALLY one that's built around healing.  Even the level 34 Mage Bolt is wrong, for a lot of reasons even if its slightly less mana efficient and .4 seconds cast slower.<br>
<br>
The problems don't come from people saying &quot;Clerics nuke better than us!!&quot; they come from people who try to say &quot;clerics SHOULD nuke better than Wizards.&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 5/18/02 7:54:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubranamanstarbinder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Branaman Starbinder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 604<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/02 8:47 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Formula is:<br>
<br>
<br>
Dmg / (mana x (cast time + recast time) ) = ratio.<br>
<br>
according to this formula, Wizards have the best nukes. In reality, Wizards still want the best nukes, but they want to play with the different values more. <br>
<br>
A high dmg, high mana but long recast time nuke (manaburn) is widely apreciated if it can be used to kill the mob in one kill.<br>
<br>
A low dmg, low mana fast casting nuke would be nice to. this to chaincast small amounts of dmg (Draughts)<br>
<br>
What we hope for is a fast casting/recasting High dmg Low mana spell. One that allows us to keep up with the DPS of the well equipped rangers and rogues.<br>
<br>
Wizards should shine in diversity on a wide range of targets. Not by comparing bane type of spells like the undead nukes of clerics, but by the ability to tailor our spells to the expected encounters. <p><center><img src="http://httpd.chello.nl/j.wensveen1/images/Branaman.jpg" width="400" alt="" border="0" align="center"><br><table><tr>
